<section>
  <h2>Progressive Enhancement</h2>
  <p>Slot a native <code>&lt;audio&gt;</code> element inside for JS-off fallback. The component hides the native element and upgrades to the full player UI when JS loads.</p>
  <code-block language="html" label="Fallback pattern">{{ basicCode | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Accessibility</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>All controls have <code>aria-label</code> attributes</li>
    <li>Play button uses <code>aria-pressed</code> to indicate state</li>
    <li>Range inputs expose <code>aria-valuemin</code>, <code>aria-valuemax</code>, and <code>aria-valuenow</code></li>
    <li>Visualizer canvas is <code>aria-hidden="true"</code></li>
    <li>Respects <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>: visualizer pauses and shows a static idle frame</li>
  </ul>
</section>

